<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-07-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-07-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="138" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                        <head>No. 134.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Flores</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Personal.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington, D. C.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-07-04"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 4, 1885</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft">To Secretary <hi rend="smallcaps">Bayard</hi>:</p>
                        <p>With the announcement of amnesty I am directed to request that the
                            Iroquois should be altogether withdrawn even from the neighboring port
                            of Payta, a measure which I trust will prove of great mutual advantage.
                            A prompt answer will oblige.</p>
                        <closer><signed>FLORES.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>